name: Creeper
description: A creeper is a common hostile mob that silently approaches players and explodes.

name: Sheep
description: Sheep are common passive mobs that supply wool and mutton and are found in many of the grassy biomes.

name: Zombie
description: Zombies are common undead hostile mobs that deal melee damage and attack in groups.

name: Skeleton
description: A skeleton is a common undead hostile mob equipped with a bow.

name: Enderman
description: An enderman is a neutral mob found in all four dimensions. Endermen can teleport and pick up blocks.

name: Villager
description: Villagers are passive mobs that inhabit villages, work at their professions, breed, and interact with each other.

name: Wither Skeleton
description: Wither skeletons are tall variants of skeletons equipped with stone swords and found in nether fortresses.

name: Magma Cube
description: A magma cube is a hostile mob found in the Nether. A magma cube behaves similarly to a slime, but has higher jumps and more powerful hits.

name: Slime
description: Slimes are bouncy, cube-shaped hostile mobs that spawn deep underground in particular chunks, or at night in swamp biomes.

name: Shulker
description: Shulkers are box-shaped hostile mobs found in end cities.

name: Endermite
description: An endermite is the smallest hostile mob. An endermite emits purple 'portal' particles.

name: Ender Dragon
description: The ender dragon is a gigantic flying hostile boss mob found when first entering the End.

name: Piglin Brute
description: A piglin brute is a hostile and stronger variant of piglins that appears in all types of bastion remnants.

name: Wither
description: The wither is a player-constructed undead hostile boss mob that floats and shoots explosive skulls at players and mobs.

name: Warden
description: The warden is a hostile mob summoned by sculk shriekers. They are completely blind, and thus rely on vibrations and their sense of smell to identify players and other mobs.

name: Ghast
description: A ghast is a large white floating ghost-like hostile mob in the Nether that shoots explosive fireballs at the player.

name: Drowned
description: Drowned are common underwater zombie variants that spawn in oceans and rivers, or when zombies drown.

name: Obsidian
description: An obsidian block used to create Nether portals.
